## 🧠 About the Project

Phishing attacks account for over **90% of data breaches** worldwide. Attackers create convincing fake websites to steal credentials, financial details, and personal information — and traditional rule-based filters increasingly fail to keep up.

This project solves that problem with **machine learning**. Instead of relying on blacklists that go stale, the model learns the structural patterns that make a URL suspicious — domain age, redirect chains, anchor ratios, HTTPS usage, and 26 more signals — and generalises to URLs it has never seen before.

### Why machine learning?

| Approach | Limitation |
|----------|-----------|
| Blacklist filtering | Only catches known phishing sites |
| Rule-based heuristics | Brittle and easy to bypass |
| ✅ Machine Learning | Learns patterns, generalises to new threats |

### What makes this project stand out?

- **30 handcrafted features** covering URL structure, domain intelligence, HTML content, and web reputation
- **10 models benchmarked** head-to-head on the same dataset
- **97.4% accuracy** with 99.4% recall — nearly every phishing URL is caught
- **Production-ready Flask app** — live web interface, Heroku-deployable

---

