## ⚙️ How It Works

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        USER INPUT                           │
│              Paste any URL into the web form                │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
                           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   FEATURE EXTRACTION                        │
│   FeatureExtraction class analyses the URL across 4 layers  │
│                                                             │
│   ① URL Structure     ② Domain Intelligence                │
│   ③ HTML Content      ④ Web Reputation                     │
│                                                             │
│              Outputs: 30 numerical features                 │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
                           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              GRADIENT BOOSTING CLASSIFIER                   │
│         Pre-trained on 11,055 labelled URLs                 │
│     Outputs: class prediction + probability score           │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
                           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                       RESULT                                │
│        ✅  "85.3% safe to visit"                           │
│        ⚠️  "12.1% safe — likely phishing"                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## 🧮 The 30 Features

The feature engine extracts signals across four layers of analysis:

### 🔗 Layer 1 — URL Structure (7 features)

| # | Feature | Signal |
|---|---------|--------|
| 1 | IP Address in URL | Phishers use IPs to bypass domain reputation checks |
| 2 | URL Length | Legitimate URLs average ~54 chars; phishing URLs are often longer |
| 3 | URL Shortening Service | Services like bit.ly are used to hide malicious destinations |
| 4 | `@` Symbol | Forces browser to ignore everything before `@` |
| 5 | Redirecting `//` | Double-slash beyond position 7 signals a redirect |
| 6 | Prefix/Suffix `-` in Domain | Hyphenated domains mimic legitimate brands (e.g. `pay-pal.com`) |
| 7 | Sub-domain Count | Deeply nested sub-domains are a common phishing pattern |

### 🌐 Layer 2 — Domain Intelligence (5 features)

| # | Feature | Signal |
|---|---------|--------|
| 8 | HTTPS Protocol | Absence of HTTPS is a red flag |
| 9 | Domain Registration Length | Short registration duration indicates a throwaway domain |
| 10 | Favicon Source | Favicon loaded from an external domain reveals spoofing |
| 11 | Non-Standard Port | Unusual ports used to bypass standard traffic filters |
| 12 | HTTPS Token in Domain | "https" in the domain name itself is a deception tactic |

### 🖥️ Layer 3 — HTML and JavaScript (11 features)

| # | Feature | Signal |
|---|---------|--------|
| 13 | Request URL Ratio | High % of external resources (images, audio) signals cloning |
| 14 | Anchor URL Ratio | Links pointing to different domains than the host |
| 15 | Script/Link Tag Ratio | Disproportionate external scripts |
| 16 | Server Form Handler | Forms submitting to `about:blank` or off-domain |
| 17 | Info Email (`mailto:`) | Use of `mailto:` in forms instead of server handlers |
| 18 | Abnormal URL | Host name does not match WHOIS registration data |
| 19 | Website Forwarding | More than 2 redirects is suspicious; 4+ is highly suspicious |
| 20 | Status Bar Customisation | `onmouseover` used to disguise the real link destination |
| 21 | Disable Right Click | JavaScript block on right-click to prevent inspection |
| 22 | Popup Windows | Aggressive `alert()` usage to harvest credentials |
| 23 | Iframe Redirection | Hidden iframes loading malicious payloads |

### 📈 Layer 4 — Web Reputation (7 features)

| # | Feature | Signal |
|---|---------|--------|
| 24 | Age of Domain | Phishing domains are typically < 6 months old |
| 25 | DNS Record | No DNS record is a strong indicator of a fake domain |
| 26 | Website Traffic | Low Alexa rank suggests an obscure or newly created site |
| 27 | Page Rank | Low PageRank correlates with phishing |
| 28 | Google Index | Unindexed pages are often malicious |
| 29 | Links Pointing to Page | Very few backlinks indicate a brand-new fake site |
| 30 | Statistical Report | URL/IP matched against known phishing blacklists |

---

## 📊 Model Benchmarks

Ten classifiers were trained and evaluated on identical train/test splits:

| Rank | Model | Accuracy | F1 Score | Recall | Precision |
|:----:|-------|:--------:|:--------:|:------:|:---------:|
| 🥇 | **Gradient Boosting Classifier** | **0.974** | **0.977** | **0.994** | **0.986** |
| 🥈 | CatBoost Classifier | 0.972 | 0.975 | 0.994 | 0.989 |
| 🥉 | XGBoost Classifier | 0.969 | 0.973 | 0.993 | 0.984 |
| 4 | Multi-layer Perceptron | 0.969 | 0.973 | 0.995 | 0.981 |
| 5 | Random Forest | 0.967 | 0.971 | 0.993 | 0.990 |
| 6 | Support Vector Machine | 0.964 | 0.968 | 0.980 | 0.965 |
| 7 | Decision Tree | 0.960 | 0.964 | 0.991 | 0.993 |
| 8 | K-Nearest Neighbors | 0.956 | 0.961 | 0.991 | 0.989 |
| 9 | Logistic Regression | 0.934 | 0.941 | 0.943 | 0.927 |
| 10 | Naive Bayes Classifier | 0.605 | 0.454 | 0.292 | 0.997 |

> GBC was selected because it achieved the highest accuracy while maintaining excellent recall — critical for a security tool where missing a phishing URL is more costly than a false alarm.

### Feature Importance

<div align="center">
<img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/79131292/144603941-19044aae-7d7b-4e9a-88a8-6adfd8626f77.png" width="75%"/>
</div>

<br/>

**Top 3 most important features:**
1. 🔒 **HTTPS** — presence or absence of a valid certificate
2. ⚓ **AnchorURL** — ratio of links pointing off-domain
3. 📡 **WebsiteTraffic** — Alexa traffic rank

