## 🏆 Results and Analysis

### Final Model Performance

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│   Gradient Boosting Classifier          │
│                                         │
│   Accuracy   ████████████████░  97.4%  │
│   F1 Score   ████████████████░  97.7%  │
│   Recall     █████████████████  99.4%  │
│   Precision  ████████████████░  98.6%  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Key Takeaways

- **99.4% Recall** — the model catches nearly every phishing URL. In security, a missed phishing site is far more dangerous than a false alarm, so recall is the most critical metric here.
- **98.6% Precision** — very few legitimate URLs are incorrectly flagged, ensuring a usable, low-friction experience.
- **Top signals** — HTTPS, AnchorURL, and WebsiteTraffic alone account for the majority of predictive power, confirming that phishers consistently fail on these dimensions.
- **Naive Bayes failure** — its low recall of 29.2% confirms that URL features are not conditionally independent, which violates the core Naive Bayes assumption.

